args:
The party struggles under a relentless Templar
assault. They think for a moment that they
have escaped the trouble with Gatov's aid,
but then find themselves trapped in an
underground waterway. But just when things
seem over, Chelle whips out her new weapon!
Surround them! Don't let them escape!
I fear we will wear ourselves out\nif we keep this up.
Yeah, and we got a whole 'nother\ngaggle of baddies headed in from\nthe other direction right now!
Are you all right, {player_name}?\nWe're here to help!
This old sword arm of mine is just\nitching for a little dance.
See how gracefully he moves; how\nhe leaves his foe not even the slightest\nopening. Truly, this is no base swordsman.
It's been a minute since I last threw my\nblade around—but while I might be a bit\nrusty, the old magic's definitely still there!
Loyal aegis of the king! Cut a way forward\nfor Gatov and our guests!
Damn it all... Fall back! Fall baaack!
I'm fine. Well, except for my aching back,\nof course. Gaaah ha ha ha ha!
Are these soldiers from some other\nunit of the Watch?
No, I had the Watch stand down. Their lives\nwould all be in great danger if they dared\nto antagonize the Church.
These people are from the royal guard.
My word... They serve the king of Grams!
Captain, how are things in the city center?
Sir, all ways in and out of the city have\nbeen sealed off and are now under the\nwatchful eye of the Templars.
I had a feeling it would come to this.\nLooks like the Pope wants to meet you\nall even at risk of killing somebody.
You'll be in for some trouble if the Church\ngets its hands on you, so you'd best get\nout of town while you still can.
I appreciate the assistance, Captain.\nGive my regards to His Majesty.

Understood, sir. And if I may be so bold,
it was an honor to witness the prodigious
skill of the Blazewolf Gatov for first time
in a great while.
Leave things here to us.\nBe cautious in the utmost, sir!
So yer in cahoots with the monarchy, too?\nWhat's yer deal, Gatov?

Oh, I'm just an old man who keeps himself
busy looking after others. I've seen a lot in
this world, but every day I'm reminded of
just how ignorant I still am.
What is our next move, Your Highness?\nWith the gates closed, we are all trapped\nlike rats.

Ah, but speaking of rats, we may still have
a play open to us. You see, my kittens tell
me there are numerous waterways that
crisscross beneath the streets of the city.
Oh, I do love a fighter who does her\nhomework. As Chelle says, you should\nbe able to slip out via an old waterway.
I know a nearby stairwell that will take\nyou underground. Follow me, please.
The waterway is just behind this gate,\nbut... Mmm, yes. That IS a problem.
Damn thing's rusted shut...\nI can't even budge it!
Our pursuers have found us once more!
We're gonna be caught with our backs\nagainst the wall! Er, or the gate, I guess.
Eee hee hee! Oh, I have been WAITING for\na chance to use this...
Uh, Chelle? What's in the bag?
If you don't want to end up with any\nadditional holes in your person,\nI suggest everyone step aside now.
Demonstrating a secret weapon, as well\nas the marvel of Chanzelia's ingenuity\nand engineering prowess!
What the blazes is...? Oh no.\nEVERYONE DOWN! NOW!

I'd call that test-fire a rousing success,
though I'll need more mana to keep the
barrel sway in control. Best to contact
R&D right away and...
Yes? What are you all staring at?\nJust go through the gate already.
Chelle? What is that big...tube thing?
I'm glad you asked! This is a manacaster\nthat was recently excavated, restored,\nand upgraded in Chanzelia.

It boasts an excellent rate of fire, great
power, and unrivaled accuracy. And thanks
to the power of mana, it's collapsible and
light—even a proper lady can carry it.
It is a truly special manacaster—and one\neminently suited to one of my standing.\nEeee hee hee hee hee!
Remind me to never get on your sister's\nbad side—or, like, ever be alone in a\nroom with her or anything.

Aaaah ha ha! A most splendid weapon—
and just what I would have expected
you to wield, Chelle! Thanks to you,
the door is open. Come then, in we go.
Okay everyone, let's hurry into the\nunderground waterway while we can!
